Former official Keith Hackett has spoken out on the referee's decisions that marred Saturday's 1-1 draw between Chelsea and Burnley, siding with Jose Mourinho's version of events.

Chelsea claim they were denied two penalties before Nemanja Matic was sent off for his aggressive reaction to a career threatening foul by Ashley Barnes - who should have already been sent off for a foul on Branislav Ivanovic.

Hackett slammed referee Martin Atkinson for a ‘pretty appalling performance’ while claiming the Serbian midfielder was fortunate not to have suffered a broken leg following Barnes' challenge. 

